	 <tr><td colspan=1  style='font-size: 9.5px;'>498 threads, <a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=4&start=0>1</a> <a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=4&start=25>2</a> <a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=4&start=50>3</a> <a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=4&start=75>4</a> <a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=4&start=100>5</a> <a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=4&start=125>6</a> <a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=4&start=150>7</a> <a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=4&start=175>8</a> <a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=4&start=200>9</a> <a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=4&start=225>10</a> <a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=4&start=250>11</a> <a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=4&start=275>12</a> <a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=4&start=300>13</a> <a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=4&start=325>14</a> <a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=4&start=350>15</a> <a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=4&start=375>16</a> <a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=4&start=400>17</a> <a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=4&start=425>18</a> <a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=4&start=450>19</a> <a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=4&start=475>20</a>  page(s) long</td><td  style='font-size: 9.5px;' align=right>&nbsp;<a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=4&start=25>Next Page</a></td></tr></table></form><a id=fs8 href=/strategy/classes.html?class=4>Root thread</a><table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=96918135820661></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96918135820661><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj>Spell Analysis 1 - 10</span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=865><span id=Sage>Ezzlan</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>38 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Sep 17th 5:02 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.30]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I only have so long to write, but here is my own analysis of the first 15 levels worth of songs, Take it as my own opinion, but I think its a pretty worthwhile guide to beginning bards to find what you should save your money for and what you should spend on armor ;)  BTW I used eq.castersrealm so I did not get mixed up in the order, And remember this is only from a level 10ish point of view spells change as time goes on, yours may differ.<br><br>More to come later<br><br>1. Chant of battle - a good buff that increases the strength, ac, and dex of everyone in the party, Making it a great buff for when you have melee people in your group, and at these levels that even includes you, The STR will improve your Attack rating, ensuring the mobs go down quicker, the small amount of ac will help you stay alive a bit longer, and the dex will help you improve you skills quicker (abashi said that dex improves the rate of weapon skill increases, but who ever believes him anyways hehehe not to mention if someone gets a nice low level proccing weapon like a dagger of dropping or is a bit twinked)<br><br>2. Chords of Dissonance - this spell has had a love/hate relationship with me. You most likely will find similar results, yes, the damage is nice, and since it is a dot (death over time spell) it is twistable (I'm not going to explain twisting, you'll have to consult another guide), The damage is ok, but much much better when using your stringed instrument, Now If you are twisting instruments you'll be happy to know this is the same skill that hymn of restoration uses, therefore you won't have to switch instruments but to sing your 3rd song, Unless of course you are using a 3rd string song, but that won't be useful till later ;) For the amount of damage this song is doing its not that much of a taunt honestly, I think that beneficial spells have a higher taunt value, because they are affecting you 6 times (if you are in a full group) where the damage spell is only effecting your aggro with 1 mob.<br><br>3. Jaxan's Jig o' Vigor - fairly useless until later when the warriors are swinging their big ol' 2 handed axes that weigh 30 stones<br><br>4. Lyssa's Locating Lyric - a valuable spell pun intended, You can always earn money by finding someones corpse, plus you can head to your corpse faster on a recovery run because it puts you right in the right direction. Why not go off-road ;)<br><br>5. Selo's accelerondo - Train O' Death Song - This song is the highest taunt song we have, don't sing it if you already have the mob on you, let someone taunt off you, equip the drum FIRST, and then turn on this song , and be outa range of that orc/gnoll/whatever  Sure this will allow you to run faster than anything you'd be fighting, but not if you are at 10% health, The high aggro is because it is snare in reverse, snare spells aggro alot, as does this spell.<br><br>6. Hymn of Restoration - purchase immediatly, sure its not a heal spell, but a regeneration spell, but once you get your strings maxxed at 8, its as good as what any healer is casting, ;) although a bit high on the taunt value, if you have someone else distracting the mob, you should still be able to get this off with little problem, plus if you are soloing at these levels your downtime will be basically nil.<br><br>7. Jonathon's Whistling Warsong - Definatly worth purchase, this song will enable you to do more damage than anyone else, because no one else can get haste effects (bar twinking) till enchanters start casting it at 16 (and at that level they don't have a large enough mana pool to cast it enough), No one has a very reliable dual wield, so everyone else is only using 1 weapon like you, Too bad your ac is not as good as a real tank, at least your damage output is nice, basically it turns us into a monk ;) Its use in a group is limited unless you are the primary damage dealer (aka grouped with a shaman enchanter and cleric or something like that)<br><br>8. Kelin's Lugubrious Lament - Ok spell in my experience, best used on a camp of blues, and if its resisted which is not that bad, and they charge at you , you should have enough time to turn on selo and high-tail it out of there, I used this spell in Lesser Faydark, If you have a druid, MAKE them Harmo the mobs, there is no reason not to, and if they don't realize the power of the harmony spell, teach them quickly or find a new druid (no offense all your tree hugging droods hehehe)<br><br>9. Elemental Rhythms - don't buy it yet, wait till you are going to be fighting casters, their fire spells, or if fighting a shaman mob their cold spells will tear you up, but not if you resist it, absolutely essential against evil eyes, if someone is charmed you are toast, but again, not useful till later. Great on dragon raids or so I've been told<br><br>10. Anthem De Arms - this is the pinnacle of this guide, and the pinnacle of power on this list, You can give a haste effect to all members of your party, when grouped with a bunch of damage dealers, aka monks and rogues, you'll find this spell the most useful, Great for twisting with chant of battle and hymn of restoration when your melee heavy and light on healing/buffers.<br><br>Well I hoped you liked these first 10 spells of my own experiences, and I hope anyone starting a new bard finds it useful.<br><br>But don't waste all your money on spells either, perhaps leave out #8 and 9 to buy yourself an additional piece of banded, You should have at least a few pieces by the time you reach 10th level. <br><br>&nbsp;<br>Ezzlan 25th ENC Brell<br>Antarius 35th Bard Terris-Thule</td></tr>
